library(readr)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(stringr)



setwd("~/rprojects/TidyTuesday/2022-02-22")


#get file
freedom <- readr::read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2022/2022-02-22/freedom.csv')

#parameters
col_low <- "#FA7F08"
col_high <- "#348888"
col_mid <- "#9EF8EE"
bck_clr <- "grey20"
seg_size <- 0.01


#need to set up so that lowest number is actually bigger here
freedom %>%
  mutate(CL = 8 - CL,
         PR = 8 - PR) %>%
  filter(year==2020 ) %>%
  group_by(PR, CL, Region_Name) %>%
  summarise(total=n())%>%
  mutate(prod = -CL * -PR) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=PR, y=CL, size=total, color=prod)) +
  scale_color_gradient2(low = col_low, high = col_high, mid = col_mid, midpoint = 24) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(vars(Region_Name))+
  geom_text(aes(label=total), size =4,  color ="black") +
  #annotate("text", x=4, y=-.25, label = "Civil Liberites", fontface ="bold", size =3) +
  #annotate("text", x =-.25, y =4, label = "Political Rights", angle = 90, fontface = "bold", size =3) +
  guides(color="none", size = "none") +
  scale_size(range= c (2,10)) +
  labs (title = "2020 Situation",
        caption= "Inspiration https://github.com/cnicault/tidytuesday",
        y= "Civil Liberties", 
        x = "Political Rights") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size =15, family = "sans"))

#Changed ordering of x axis but left the rest the same

#get 2010 values
CL_2010<-freedom %>% 
  filter(Region_Name == 'Africa') %>% 
  filter(year == 2010) %>% 
  select(country, CL) %>% 
  rename(CL_2010=CL)

  
#clean and manipulate data
#Add in the change in civil liberties since 2010
data<-freedom %>% 
  filter(Region_Name == 'Africa') %>% 
  filter(year == 2020) %>% 
  left_join(CL_2010, by='country') %>% 
  mutate(diff = CL-CL_2010) %>% 
  mutate(balance=
           case_when(diff>0 ~'negative',
                     diff<0 ~'positive',
                     diff == 0 ~'equal')) %>% 
  #select(country, CL, CL_2010, diff, balance) %>% 
  filter(balance == 'negative'| balance=='positive')


data$country[data$country == "CÃƒÂ´te dÃ¢â‚¬â„¢Ivoire"]<-"Cote d'Ivoire"

#plot
ggplot(data, aes(y = reorder(country, diff), x = diff, color=balance))+
  geom_segment(aes(yend = country), xend = -4, x=3, color = 'grey70', alpha = 0.3, size=5)+
  geom_segment(aes(yend = country), xend=0, size=5)+
  geom_point(size=4.5)+
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, size=2, color='grey35')+
  expand_limits(x=c(-4,3.75), y = 20.5)+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(-2, -1, 1, 2))+
  
  #add countries in chart
  geom_text(aes(label=country), x = -4, hjust=0, size=3.5, color="grey3")+
  geom_segment(aes(yend=country), x = -4, xend=-2.5, size=5, alpha = 0.2)+
  
  #change colors
  scale_color_manual(values=c("orange3", "steelblue4"))+
  scale_x_reverse()+
  guides(color="none", y="none")+
  labs(y=NULL, x="Change in Civil Liberty Rating (lower = More Freedom)",
       title = " Civil Freedom in Africa",
       subtitle = "   Changes in Civil Liberty from 2010 to 2020",
       
       caption = " Source: United Nations and Freedom House and https://github.com/lpicci96/visualizations/blob/main/%23TidyTuesday/scripts/tidy_tuesday_2-22.Rmd")+
  
  #theme
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(plot.background = element_rect(fill = "Aliceblue", color="Aliceblue"),
        panel.grid = element_blank(),

)+
